{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Sensors","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Sensors"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Our devices have tons of sensors:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC19-426-sensors","type":"image"}]},{"anchor":"What-is-an-Activity-Classification","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"What is an Activity Classification?"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Activity Classification is a task that allows us to recognize our pre-defined set of physical actions that the user does with their devices.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the session, the presenter shows us an example of a Fressbee throws classifier.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"An example of activity data (it’s a csv table with time stamps and ","type":"text"},{"code":"x, y, z","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" values):","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC19-426-training","type":"image"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In Create ML we can filter which axis of which acceleration\/rotation we should consider for the training, we can also define a Prediction Window Size to let Create ML know how much is the size of the sample to analyze (this way we can have multiple gestures\/measurements in one table)."}]},{"anchor":"Best-practices","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Best practices"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use relevant sensor for your motion (understand your motion)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Collect irrelevant motions as “other”, to avoid false positive"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Provide balanced classes (same number of samples for each class\/category)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[